The Jayhawks are an American alternative country and rock band. They released seven studio albums, including five on the American Recordings label. In 2009, Olson and Louris began a duet tour run at the Varsity theater in Minneapolis, and Marc Perlman played live with John Wesley Harding at the 7th Street Entry. Members continue to collaborate on live shows and studio projects.
